abstract: Attackers descend on vegan cafe in nation of Georgia and pelt patrons with sausages, raising fears of growing culture war; some speculate attack relates to nationalist resentment against Western values.
lead_paragraph: Analysts cautioned it was too early to say whether the episode in Georgia’s capital was a revolt against veganism or part of a nationalist attack against Western liberal values.

headline.main: Patrons of Vegan Cafe Are Pelted With Meat in Tbilisi, Georgia
headline.print_headline: Wursts Fly at Vegans in Georgia Culture War
